did.unittitle: Rice University President David W. Leebron Inauguration records
did.abstract: Correspondence, calendars of events, event programs, invitations, agendas, mailing lists, minutes, brochures, testimonials and more related to the celebration of the 2004 inauguration of Rice University's seventh president.

bioghist.head: Historical Sketch
bioghist.p: For each incoming Rice president, an Inaugural Committee is formed which works with the Board of Governors and the President's Office to plan the numerous presidential welcoming events and celebrations. After the inauguration, the committee is released from duty. David W. Leebron took office as Rice University's seventh president on July 1, 2004. On Saturday, October 2, 2004, he was officially inaugurated into that post. Due to inclement weather conditions and heat and humidity, the inaugural proceedings were held at 9:30 a.m. in the Rice Gymnasium, Autry Court. The inaugural dinner was held at the Warwick Hotel. The Rice Concert Band, the Rice Chorale, the Shepherd School Brass Ensemble, and Melody Johnson, a Shepherd School soprano, provided the music for the occasion. Arthur Gottschalk, chair of composition and theory with the Shepherd School of Music, composed a special fanfare for the inauguration ceremony. More than 200 delegates representing universities and learned societies from around the world attended the inauguration, as did such distinguished guests as the consuls of Jordan, Ukraine, and Saudi Arabia; Ambassador Edward Djerejian; and Congresswoman Sheila Jackson Lee.

David Leebron was born in 1956 in Philadelphia. He earned a bachelor of art's degree (1976) and doctorate of jurisprudence (1979) from Harvard University. After college Leebron clerked at the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals and taught at the UCLA School of Law and New York University. From 1981 to 1983, he practiced privately with the New York law firm of Cleary, Gottlieb, Steen & Hamilton. In 1989 Leebron joined the faculty of the Columbia Law School. He later became the Lucy G. Moses Professor of Law and dean of the law school, a position he remained in until his selection as Rice's president. Leebron is married to Y. Ping Sun. They have two children.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, calendars of events, event programs, invitations, agendas, mailing lists, minutes, brochures, testimonials and more related to the celebration of the 2004 inauguration of Rice University's seventh president. The Leebron Inaugural Committee created or maintained the bulk of this material.

userestrict.p: Permission to publish material from the Leebron Inaugural Committee records must be obtained from the Woodson Research Center, Fondren Library.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Series I is made up of the inaugural committee's working papers. This material consists of committee lists; faculty, institutional, foundation, and dignitary mailing lists; meetings and agendas; thank you notes; the inauguration schedule; and information related to the 1993 inauguration of Rice's sixth president, S. Malcolm Gillis. There is limited correspondence. This series is organized alphabetically.

did.unittitle: Mailing Lists – Learned Societies and Associations

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Series II includes investiture invitations; investiture programs; investiture tickets; and internal documents related to digital recording of inaugural events, a timeline of inaugural events, transportation, parking, line of procession, regalia, and the presidential medal. Series II also includes information about the delegates who were invited to or who attended the inaugural events. Delegate lists are provided both numerically by the founding date and alphabetically by the name of the institution or society. This series also includes other types of information provided for delegates, such as a schedule of events, details about transportation, Houston events, and robing. This series is arranged alphabetically.

did.unittitle: Investiture summons (5 copies, 1 signed by E. William Barnett, Chair, Board of Trustees)

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Series III is made up of events connected with the inauguration of David W. Leebron. It is arranged chronologically. Events covered include an art exhibit, cocktail reception, alumni/student reception, inaugural concert, and post-investiture luncheon and dinner.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Series IV contains a list of inaugural expenses incurred and is arranged alphabetically. This includes expenses related to the investiture itself, as well as those related to printing, publicity, events, and administration. A media plan, copies of printed materials such as the Leebron Family insert and a visitor's guide that went into each delegate's package, and a typescript of a commemorative book about Rice and the inaugural are also within this series.
